If you look at the error message you see:

&gt; Unable to locate element: {&quot;method&quot;:&quot;css selector&quot;,&quot;selector&quot;:**&quot;.btn\ _modal&quot;**}

Note the slash that&#39;s been added to the selector. The element is actually two classes applied to one element; &quot;btn&quot; and &quot;_modal&quot;. The `By.classname()` will only except a single name so it&#39;s trying to put them together and obviously failing.

The best way to handle it would be use `By.cssSelector()` and use dot notation:

    driver.findElement(By.cssSelector(&quot;.btn._modal&quot;)).click();

